      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Fix stale auto-fallback origin model selection",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Adds a shared stale auto-fallback-origin classifier so reply and agent-command selection agree when recorded fallback origin no longer matches the current primary.\n- Defers reply-side model/auth cleanup until after read-only slash/inline actions have dispatched and a real run is about to start.\n- Guards deferred reply cleanup against post-selection session changes so mixed `/model ...` directives and concurrent row updates are not overwritten.\n- Prepares agent-command attempts with stale fallback model/auth cleared in memory, then persists durable cleanup only after a successful visible run and only if the store row still exactly matches the stale fallback pin captured at selection time.\n\n## Maintainer feedback addressed\n- One prepared selection result now carries reset reason and persistence behavior through the reply turn.\n- Stale-origin repair no longer emits the disallowed-allowlist reset event.\n- Preserve-state/non-mutating agent-command runs strip fallback auth for the primary attempt without writing durable cleanup.\n- Deferred reply cleanup is guarded against concurrent user model switches and mixed inline model directives.\n- Direct agent-command cleanup captures the stale row fields at selection time and refuses to persist if the current store row has changed to a different stale auto-fallback pin.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- Behavior or issue addressed: stale auto-fallback model pins whose recorded fallback origin no longer matches the current primary were being treated as active stored overrides; the fix prepares the primary selection for the next real run and defers durable cleanup until the run boundary without overwriting user-owned or newer auto-owned model changes made after selection.\n- Real environment tested: local OpenClaw checkout on branch `codex/92776-prepared-model-selection-boundary`, commit `ebe706b1ba`, running the patched runtime module through Node 24 with `tsx` from the repository dependencies.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch: ran `node --import tsx --input-type=module` from the repository root and imported `isStaleAutoFallbackOriginOverride` from the patched source. The command exercised the direct cleanup risk ClawSweeper identified: a stale row changed to a different stale auto-fallback pin before cleanup.\n- Evidence after fix (screenshot, recording, terminal capture, console output, redacted runtime log, linked artifact, or copied live output): copied terminal output from the live Node command:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"proof\": \"direct-stale-auto-fallback-exact-row-guard\",\n  \"head\": \"ebe706b1ba\",\n  \"oldBroadPredicate\": {\n    \"capturedStale\": true,\n    \"changedRowStillStale\": true\n  },\n  \"exactGuard\": {\n    \"capturedMatches\": true,\n    \"changedMatches\": false\n  },\n  \"observedResult\": \"changed stale row remains stale under the broad predicate but fails the exact captured-row guard, so direct cleanup shouldPersist refuses to persist cleared model/auth fields.\"\n}\n```\n\n- Observed result after fix: the unchanged captured stale pin can be cleaned up, but if the direct-session row changes to a different stale auto-fallback pin before cleanup, the exact guard fails and cleanup does not persist cleared model/auth fields over the newer row.\n- What was not tested: no live external provider API call was sent; this proof exercises the local OpenClaw stale-origin classifier and direct cleanup guard boundary.\n- Proof limitations or environment constraints: the proof uses redacted throwaway session fields to avoid publishing real auth profile names.\n- Before evidence: ClawSweeper review on this PR identified that the previous direct cleanup `shouldPersist` accepted any stale auto-fallback row, so a different stale row could still be overwritten.\n\n## Verification\n- pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/agents/agent-command.ts src/agents/agent-command.live-model-switch.test.ts\n- node scripts/test-projects.mjs src/agents/agent-command.live-model-switch.test.ts\n- node scripts/test-projects.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/model-selection.test.ts src/agents/agent-command.live-model-switch.test.ts\n- node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/directive-handling.model.test.ts\n- pnpm tsgo:core\n- pnpm tsgo:test:src\n- pnpm lint:core\n- CI=1 pnpm check:changed -- --base upstream/main --head HEAD\n\nFixes #92776\nSupersedes #92790\n",
        "branch": "codex/92776-prepared-model-selection-boundary",
